

    
       
      Passage taken directly from my International Environmental Law casebook, part of an excerpt from Ambassador Tommy Koh's reflections on a United Nations environmental summit:  "At 4:00 am, after eight hours in the chair, I was desperate to go to the toilet.  I also sensed that there was a lot of tension in the room.  I announced that we would recess the meeting for five minutes in order to enable me to make a discharge of a non-toxic waste.  I promised to do it in an environmentally safe and sound manner.  The delegates broke into laughter and the meeting resumed in a better mood."  File that under too much information...
      
